column2: "You... are not the Miko-sama, aren't you? What a dissapointment."
"If only Miko-sama would assist us, the Kuronians will be of no match even with their superior numbers."
"He is not the only one. The Shironians are all of the same. Uttering such words with ignorant bliss."
"Indubitably, the Kuronians are at fault for this attack. Be that as it may, they art fools."
"Doubtless, they art manipulated and deceived by those troublesome children. Nevertheless, 'tis absurd."
"And the Kuronian Lord remains indifferent towards the situation as well."
"Howbeit, Shironians and Kuronians, both are helpless fools."
"To dismiss all attempts at peace, and charge onto the path of war in such haste."
"Ah... Fools, such folly. The mothers and fathers shall weep to the Great River."
"Both of you. Do not falter for worry of this planet. Have at these fools."
"Sukunahime... I wonder if something happened in the past?"
